<td id="_5ca90fd9-3396-f779-4d6a-ca9dacd195f4" valign="top" align="left"><eref type="inline" bibitemid="zanthier" citeas="[2]"/><fn id="_9dab5e3f-36ef-c7ec-ced0-cb49715a2058" reference="a"><p id="_dfe09a9a-3296-4587-3cc4-ca86a2c823a3">From the least square procedure it turned out that the value and the uncertainty given in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="zanthier" citeas="[2]"/> is not compatible with the remaining data. Thus the uncertainty given in the original publication <eref type="inline" bibitemid="zanthier" citeas="[2]"/> was increased to <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
